put an incessant belt of circumnavigations round it; peeped in                  chg na vaprffnag oryg bs pvephzanivtngvbaf ebhaq vg; crrcrq va
at Behring's Straits; and in all seasons and all oceans declared                ng Oruevat'f Fgenvgf; naq va nyy frnfbaf naq nyy bprnaf qrpynerq
everlasting war with the mightiest animated mass that has survived the          rireynfgvat jne jvgu gur zvtugvrfg navzngrq znff gung unf fheivirq gur
flood; most monstrous and most mountainous! That Himmalehan, salt-sea           sybbq; zbfg zbafgebhf naq zbfg zbhagnvabhf! Gung Uvzznyruna, fnyg-frn
Mastodon, clothed with such portentousness of unconscious power, that           Znfgbqba, pybgurq jvgu fhpu cbegragbhfarff bs hapbafpvbhf cbjre, gung
his very panics are more to be dreaded than his most fearless and               uvf irel cnavpf ner zber gb or qernqrq guna uvf zbfg srneyrff naq
malicious assaults!                                                             znyvpvbhf nffnhygf!
                                                                                
And thus have these naked Nantucketers, these sea hermits, issuing from         Naq guhf unir gurfr anxrq Anaghpxrgref, gurfr frn urezvgf, vffhvat sebz
their ant-hill in the sea, overrun and conquered the watery world like          gurve nag-uvyy va gur frn, bireeha naq pbadhrerq gur jngrel jbeyq yvxr
so many Alexanders; parcelling out among them the Atlantic, Pacific, and        fb znal Nyrknaqref; cnepryyvat bhg nzbat gurz gur Ngynagvp, Cnpvsvp, naq
Indian oceans, as the three pirate powers did Poland. Let America add           Vaqvna bprnaf, nf gur guerr cvengr cbjref qvq Cbynaq. Yrg Nzrevpn nqq
Mexico to Texas, and pile Cuba upon Canada; let the English overswarm           Zrkvpb gb Grknf, naq cvyr Phon hcba Pnanqn; yrg gur Ratyvfu birefjnez
all India, and hang out their blazing banner from the sun; two thirds           nyy Vaqvn, naq unat bhg gurve oynmvat onaare sebz gur fha; gjb guveqf
of this terraqueous globe are the Nantucketer's. For the sea is his; he         bs guvf greendhrbhf tybor ner gur Anaghpxrgre'f. Sbe gur frn vf uvf; ur
owns it, as Emperors own empires; other seamen having but a right of            bjaf vg, nf Rzcrebef bja rzcverf; bgure frnzra univat ohg n evtug bs
way through it. Merchant ships are but extension bridges; armed ones but        jnl guebhtu vg. Zrepunag fuvcf ner ohg rkgrafvba oevqtrf; nezrq barf ohg
floating forts; even pirates and privateers, though following the sea           sybngvat sbegf; rira cvengrf naq cevingrref, gubhtu sbyybjvat gur frn
as highwaymen the road, they but plunder other ships, other fragments of        nf uvtujnlzra gur ebnq, gurl ohg cyhaqre bgure fuvcf, bgure sentzragf bs
the land like themselves, without seeking to draw their living from the         gur ynaq yvxr gurzfryirf, jvgubhg frrxvat gb qenj gurve yvivat sebz gur
bottomless deep itself. The Nantucketer, he alone resides and riots on          obggbzyrff qrrc vgfrys. Gur Anaghpxrgre, ur nybar erfvqrf naq evbgf ba
the sea; he alone, in Bible language, goes down to it in ships; to and          gur frn; ur nybar, va Ovoyr ynathntr, tbrf qbja gb vg va fuvcf; gb naq
fro ploughing it as his own special plantation. THERE is his home; THERE        seb cybhtuvat vg nf uvf bja fcrpvny cynagngvba. GURER vf uvf ubzr; GURER
lies his business, which a Noah's flood would not interrupt, though it          yvrf uvf ohfvarff, juvpu n Abnu'f sybbq jbhyq abg vagreehcg, gubhtu vg
overwhelmed all the millions in China. He lives on the sea, as prairie          birejuryzrq nyy gur zvyyvbaf va Puvan. Ur yvirf ba gur frn, nf cenvevr
cocks in the prairie; he hides among the waves, he climbs them as               pbpxf va gur cenvevr; ur uvqrf nzbat gur jnirf, ur pyvzof gurz nf
chamois hunters climb the Alps. For years he knows not the land; so             punzbvf uhagref pyvzo gur Nycf. Sbe lrnef ur xabjf abg gur ynaq; fb
that when he comes to it at last, it smells like another world, more            gung jura ur pbzrf gb vg ng ynfg, vg fzryyf yvxr nabgure jbeyq, zber
strangely than the moon would to an Earthsman. With the landless gull,          fgenatryl guna gur zbba jbhyq gb na Rnegufzna. Jvgu gur ynaqyrff thyy,
that at sunset folds her wings and is rocked to sleep between billows;          gung ng fhafrg sbyqf ure jvatf naq vf ebpxrq gb fyrrc orgjrra ovyybjf;
so at nightfall, the Nantucketer, out of sight of land, furls his sails,        fb ng avtugsnyy, gur Anaghpxrgre, bhg bs fvtug bs ynaq, sheyf uvf fnvyf,
and lays him to his rest, while under his very pillow rush herds of             naq ynlf uvz gb uvf erfg, juvyr haqre uvf irel cvyybj ehfu ureqf bs
walruses and whales.                                                            jnyehfrf naq junyrf.
                                                                                
                                                                                
                                                                                
