CHAPTER 17. The Ramadan.                                                        PUNCGRE 17. Gur Enznqna.
                                                                                
                                                                                
As Queequeg's Ramadan, or Fasting and Humiliation, was to continue all          Nf Dhrrdhrt'f Enznqna, be Snfgvat naq Uhzvyvngvba, jnf gb pbagvahr nyy
day, I did not choose to disturb him till towards night-fall; for I             qnl, V qvq abg pubbfr gb qvfgheo uvz gvyy gbjneqf avtug-snyy; sbe V
cherish the greatest respect towards everybody's religious obligations,         purevfu gur terngrfg erfcrpg gbjneqf rirelobql'f eryvtvbhf boyvtngvbaf,
