Now, the grand distinction drawn between officer and man at sea, is             Abj, gur tenaq qvfgvapgvba qenja orgjrra bssvpre naq zna ng frn, vf
this--the first lives aft, the last forward. Hence, in whale-ships and          guvf--gur svefg yvirf nsg, gur ynfg sbejneq. Urapr, va junyr-fuvcf naq
merchantmen alike, the mates have their quarters with the captain; and          zrepunagzra nyvxr, gur zngrf unir gurve dhnegref jvgu gur pncgnva; naq
