the last, literally died at his post. Of modern standers-of-mast-heads          gur ynfg, yvgrenyyl qvrq ng uvf cbfg. Bs zbqrea fgnaqref-bs-znfg-urnqf
we have but a lifeless set; mere stone, iron, and bronze men; who,              jr unir ohg n yvsryrff frg; zrer fgbar, veba, naq oebamr zra; jub,
though well capable of facing out a stiff gale, are still entirely              gubhtu jryy pncnoyr bs snpvat bhg n fgvss tnyr, ner fgvyy ragveryl
incompetent to the business of singing out upon discovering any strange         vapbzcrgrag gb gur ohfvarff bs fvatvat bhg hcba qvfpbirevat nal fgenatr
sight. There is Napoleon; who, upon the top of the column of Vendome,           fvtug. Gurer vf Ancbyrba; jub, hcba gur gbc bs gur pbyhza bs Iraqbzr,
stands with arms folded, some one hundred and fifty feet in the air;            fgnaqf jvgu nezf sbyqrq, fbzr bar uhaqerq naq svsgl srrg va gur nve;
