part, is as important a one as will be found in this volume; but the            cneg, vf nf vzcbegnag n bar nf jvyy or sbhaq va guvf ibyhzr; ohg gur
leading matter of it requires to be still further and more familiarly           yrnqvat znggre bs vg erdhverf gb or fgvyy shegure naq zber snzvyvneyl
enlarged upon, in order to be adequately understood, and moreover to            raynetrq hcba, va beqre gb or nqrdhngryl haqrefgbbq, naq zberbire gb
take away any incredulity which a profound ignorance of the entire              gnxr njnl nal vaperqhyvgl juvpu n cebsbhaq vtabenapr bs gur ragver
subject may induce in some minds, as to the natural verity of the main          fhowrpg znl vaqhpr va fbzr zvaqf, nf gb gur angheny irevgl bs gur znva
points of this affair.                                                          cbvagf bs guvf nssnve.
                                                                                
I care not to perform this part of my task methodically; but shall              V pner abg gb cresbez guvf cneg bs zl gnfx zrgubqvpnyyl; ohg funyy
be content to produce the desired impression by separate citations of           or pbagrag gb cebqhpr gur qrfverq vzcerffvba ol frcnengr pvgngvbaf bs
