First: In the year 1820 the ship Essex, Captain Pollard, of Nantucket,          Svefg: Va gur lrne 1820 gur fuvc Rffrk, Pncgnva Cbyyneq, bs Anaghpxrg,
was cruising in the Pacific Ocean. One day she saw spouts, lowered her          jnf pehvfvat va gur Cnpvsvp Bprna. Bar qnl fur fnj fcbhgf, ybjrerq ure
boats, and gave chase to a shoal of sperm whales. Ere long, several of          obngf, naq tnir punfr gb n fubny bs fcrez junyrf. Rer ybat, frireny bs
the whales were wounded; when, suddenly, a very large whale escaping            gur junyrf jrer jbhaqrq; jura, fhqqrayl, n irel ynetr junyr rfpncvat
from the boats, issued from the shoal, and bore directly down upon the          sebz gur obngf, vffhrq sebz gur fubny, naq ober qverpgyl qbja hcba gur
ship. Dashing his forehead against her hull, he so stove her in, that in        fuvc. Qnfuvat uvf sberurnq ntnvafg ure uhyy, ur fb fgbir ure va, gung va
less than "ten minutes" she settled down and fell over. Not a surviving         yrff guna "gra zvahgrf" fur frggyrq qbja naq sryy bire. Abg n fheivivat
plank of her has been seen since. After the severest exposure, part of          cynax bs ure unf orra frra fvapr. Nsgre gur frirerfg rkcbfher, cneg bs
the crew reached the land in their boats. Being returned home at last,          gur perj ernpurq gur ynaq va gurve obngf. Orvat erghearq ubzr ng ynfg,
Captain Pollard once more sailed for the Pacific in command of another          Pncgnva Cbyyneq bapr zber fnvyrq sbe gur Cnpvsvp va pbzznaq bs nabgure
ship, but the gods shipwrecked him again upon unknown rocks and                 fuvc, ohg gur tbqf fuvcjerpxrq uvz ntnva hcba haxabja ebpxf naq
breakers; for the second time his ship was utterly lost, and forthwith          oernxref; sbe gur frpbaq gvzr uvf fuvc jnf hggreyl ybfg, naq sbegujvgu
