*The following are extracts from Chace's narrative: "Every fact seemed          *Gur sbyybjvat ner rkgenpgf sebz Punpr'f aneengvir: "Rirel snpg frrzrq
to warrant me in concluding that it was anything but chance which               gb jneenag zr va pbapyhqvat gung vg jnf nalguvat ohg punapr juvpu
directed his operations; he made two several attacks upon the ship, at          qverpgrq uvf bcrengvbaf; ur znqr gjb frireny nggnpxf hcba gur fuvc, ng
a short interval between them, both of which, according to their                n fubeg vagreiny orgjrra gurz, obgu bs juvpu, nppbeqvat gb gurve
direction, were calculated to do us the most injury, by being made              qverpgvba, jrer pnyphyngrq gb qb hf gur zbfg vawhel, ol orvat znqr
ahead, and thereby combining the speed of the two objects for the shock;        nurnq, naq gurerol pbzovavat gur fcrrq bs gur gjb bowrpgf sbe gur fubpx;
to effect which, the exact manoeuvres which he made were necessary. His         gb rssrpg juvpu, gur rknpg znabrhierf juvpu ur znqr jrer arprffnel. Uvf
