some one or two particulars, not at all affecting the matter presently          fbzr bar be gjb cnegvphynef, abg ng nyy nssrpgvat gur znggre cerfragyl
to be mentioned.                                                                gb or zragvbarq.
                                                                                
Now, in this history of his, Procopius mentions that, during the term           Abj, va guvf uvfgbel bs uvf, Cebpbcvhf zragvbaf gung, qhevat gur grez
of his prefecture at Constantinople, a great sea-monster was captured           bs uvf cersrpgher ng Pbafgnagvabcyr, n terng frn-zbafgre jnf pncgherq
