assertion the pirate has no solid basis to stand on.                            nffregvba gur cvengr unf ab fbyvq onfvf gb fgnaq ba.
                                                                                
But what is a GAM? You might wear out your index-finger running up and          Ohg jung vf n TNZ? Lbh zvtug jrne bhg lbhe vaqrk-svatre ehaavat hc naq
down the columns of dictionaries, and never find the word. Dr. Johnson          qbja gur pbyhzaf bs qvpgvbanevrf, naq arire svaq gur jbeq. Qe. Wbuafba
never attained to that erudition; Noah Webster's ark does not hold it.          arire nggnvarq gb gung rehqvgvba; Abnu Jrofgre'f nex qbrf abg ubyq vg.
Nevertheless, this same expressive word has now for many years been in          Arireguryrff, guvf fnzr rkcerffvir jbeq unf abj sbe znal lrnef orra va
constant use among some fifteen thousand true born Yankees. Certainly,          pbafgnag hfr nzbat fbzr svsgrra gubhfnaq gehr obea Lnaxrrf. Pregnvayl,
it needs a definition, and should be incorporated into the Lexicon. With        vg arrqf n qrsvavgvba, naq fubhyq or vapbecbengrq vagb gur Yrkvpba. Jvgu
that view, let me learnedly define it.                                          gung ivrj, yrg zr yrnearqyl qrsvar vg.
                                                                                
GAM. NOUN--A SOCIAL MEETING OF TWO (OR MORE) WHALESHIPS, GENERALLY ON A         TNZ. ABHA--N FBPVNY ZRRGVAT BS GJB (BE ZBER) JUNYRFUVCF, TRARENYYL BA N
CRUISING-GROUND; WHEN, AFTER EXCHANGING HAILS, THEY EXCHANGE VISITS BY          PEHVFVAT-TEBHAQ; JURA, NSGRE RKPUNATVAT UNVYF, GURL RKPUNATR IVFVGF OL
BOATS' CREWS; THE TWO CAPTAINS REMAINING, FOR THE TIME, ON BOARD OF ONE         OBNGF' PERJF; GUR GJB PNCGNVAF ERZNVAVAT, SBE GUR GVZR, BA OBNEQ BS BAR
SHIP, AND THE TWO CHIEF MATES ON THE OTHER.                                     FUVC, NAQ GUR GJB PUVRS ZNGRF BA GUR BGURE.
                                                                                
There is another little item about Gamming which must not be forgotten          Gurer vf nabgure yvggyr vgrz nobhg Tnzzvat juvpu zhfg abg or sbetbggra
here. All professions have their own little peculiarities of detail; so         urer. Nyy cebsrffvbaf unir gurve bja yvggyr crphyvnevgvrf bs qrgnvy; fb
has the whale fishery. In a pirate, man-of-war, or slave ship, when             unf gur junyr svfurel. Va n cvengr, zna-bs-jne, be fynir fuvc, jura
the captain is rowed anywhere in his boat, he always sits in the stern          gur pncgnva vf ebjrq naljurer va uvf obng, ur nyjnlf fvgf va gur fgrea
sheets on a comfortable, sometimes cushioned seat there, and often              furrgf ba n pbzsbegnoyr, fbzrgvzrf phfuvbarq frng gurer, naq bsgra
steers himself with a pretty little milliner's tiller decorated with            fgrref uvzfrys jvgu n cerggl yvggyr zvyyvare'f gvyyre qrpbengrq jvgu
gay cords and ribbons. But the whale-boat has no seat astern, no sofa of        tnl pbeqf naq evoobaf. Ohg gur junyr-obng unf ab frng nfgrea, ab fbsn bs
that sort whatever, and no tiller at all. High times indeed, if whaling         gung fbeg jungrire, naq ab gvyyre ng nyy. Uvtu gvzrf vaqrrq, vs junyvat
captains were wheeled about the water on castors like gouty old aldermen        pncgnvaf jrer jurryrq nobhg gur jngre ba pnfgbef yvxr tbhgl byq nyqrezra
in patent chairs. And as for a tiller, the whale-boat never admits of           va cngrag punvef. Naq nf sbe n gvyyre, gur junyr-obng arire nqzvgf bs
any such effeminacy; and therefore as in gamming a complete boat's crew         nal fhpu rssrzvanpl; naq gurersber nf va tnzzvat n pbzcyrgr obng'f perj
must leave the ship, and hence as the boat steerer or harpooneer is of          zhfg yrnir gur fuvc, naq urapr nf gur obng fgrrere be unecbbarre vf bs
the number, that subordinate is the steersman upon the occasion, and            gur ahzore, gung fhobeqvangr vf gur fgrrefzna hcba gur bppnfvba, naq
the captain, having no place to sit in, is pulled off to his visit              gur pncgnva, univat ab cynpr gb fvg va, vf chyyrq bss gb uvf ivfvg
all standing like a pine tree. And often you will notice that being             nyy fgnaqvat yvxr n cvar gerr. Naq bsgra lbh jvyy abgvpr gung orvat
conscious of the eyes of the whole visible world resting on him from            pbafpvbhf bs gur rlrf bs gur jubyr ivfvoyr jbeyq erfgvat ba uvz sebz
the sides of the two ships, this standing captain is all alive to the           gur fvqrf bs gur gjb fuvcf, guvf fgnaqvat pncgnva vf nyy nyvir gb gur
importance of sustaining his dignity by maintaining his legs. Nor is            vzcbegnapr bs fhfgnvavat uvf qvtavgl ol znvagnvavat uvf yrtf. Abe vf
this any very easy matter; for in his rear is the immense projecting            guvf nal irel rnfl znggre; sbe va uvf erne vf gur vzzrafr cebwrpgvat
steering oar hitting him now and then in the small of his back, the             fgrrevat bne uvggvat uvz abj naq gura va gur fznyy bs uvf onpx, gur
after-oar reciprocating by rapping his knees in front. He is thus               nsgre-bne erpvcebpngvat ol enccvat uvf xarrf va sebag. Ur vf guhf
completely wedged before and behind, and can only expand himself                pbzcyrgryl jrqtrq orsber naq oruvaq, naq pna bayl rkcnaq uvzfrys
sideways by settling down on his stretched legs; but a sudden, violent          fvqrjnlf ol frggyvat qbja ba uvf fgergpurq yrtf; ohg n fhqqra, ivbyrag
pitch of the boat will often go far to topple him, because length of            cvgpu bs gur obng jvyy bsgra tb sne gb gbccyr uvz, orpnhfr yratgu bs
foundation is nothing without corresponding breadth. Merely make a              sbhaqngvba vf abguvat jvgubhg pbeerfcbaqvat oernqgu. Zreryl znxr n
spread angle of two poles, and you cannot stand them up. Then, again,           fcernq natyr bs gjb cbyrf, naq lbh pnaabg fgnaq gurz hc. Gura, ntnva,
it would never do in plain sight of the world's riveted eyes, it would          vg jbhyq arire qb va cynva fvtug bs gur jbeyq'f evirgrq rlrf, vg jbhyq
never do, I say, for this straddling captain to be seen steadying               arire qb, V fnl, sbe guvf fgenqqyvat pncgnva gb or frra fgrnqlvat
himself the slightest particle by catching hold of anything with                uvzfrys gur fyvtugrfg cnegvpyr ol pngpuvat ubyq bs nalguvat jvgu
his hands; indeed, as token of his entire, buoyant self-command, he             uvf unaqf; vaqrrq, nf gbxra bs uvf ragver, ohblnag frys-pbzznaq, ur
generally carries his hands in his trowsers' pockets; but perhaps being         trarenyyl pneevrf uvf unaqf va uvf gebjfref' cbpxrgf; ohg creuncf orvat
generally very large, heavy hands, he carries them there for ballast.           trarenyyl irel ynetr, urnil unaqf, ur pneevrf gurz gurer sbe onyynfg.
Nevertheless there have occurred instances, well authenticated ones too,        Arireguryrff gurer unir bppheerq vafgnaprf, jryy nhguragvpngrq barf gbb,
where the captain has been known for an uncommonly critical moment or           jurer gur pncgnva unf orra xabja sbe na hapbzzbayl pevgvpny zbzrag be
