of the whale bears the same relation to the fully invested and padded           bs gur junyr ornef gur fnzr eryngvba gb gur shyyl vairfgrq naq cnqqrq
animal as the insect does to the chrysalis that so roundingly envelopes         navzny nf gur vafrpg qbrf gb gur puelfnyvf gung fb ebhaqvatyl rairybcrf
it. This peculiarity is strikingly evinced in the head, as in some              vg. Guvf crphyvnevgl vf fgevxvatyl rivaprq va gur urnq, nf va fbzr
part of this book will be incidentally shown. It is also very curiously         cneg bs guvf obbx jvyy or vapvqragnyyl fubja. Vg vf nyfb irel phevbhfyl
displayed in the side fin, the bones of which almost exactly answer to          qvfcynlrq va gur fvqr sva, gur obarf bs juvpu nyzbfg rknpgyl nafjre gb
the bones of the human hand, minus only the thumb. This fin has four            gur obarf bs gur uhzna unaq, zvahf bayl gur guhzo. Guvf sva unf sbhe
regular bone-fingers, the index, middle, ring, and little finger. But           erthyne obar-svatref, gur vaqrk, zvqqyr, evat, naq yvggyr svatre. Ohg
all these are permanently lodged in their fleshy covering, as the human         nyy gurfr ner creznaragyl ybqtrq va gurve syrful pbirevat, nf gur uhzna
fingers in an artificial covering. "However recklessly the whale may            svatref va na negvsvpvny pbirevat. "Ubjrire erpxyrffyl gur junyr znl
sometimes serve us," said humorous Stubb one day, "he can never be truly        fbzrgvzrf freir hf," fnvq uhzbebhf Fghoo bar qnl, "ur pna arire or gehyl
said to handle us without mittens."                                             fnvq gb unaqyr hf jvgubhg zvggraf."
                                                                                
For all these reasons, then, any way you may look at it, you must needs         Sbe nyy gurfr ernfbaf, gura, nal jnl lbh znl ybbx ng vg, lbh zhfg arrqf
conclude that the great Leviathan is that one creature in the world             pbapyhqr gung gur terng Yrivnguna vf gung bar perngher va gur jbeyq
which must remain unpainted to the last. True, one portrait may hit             juvpu zhfg erznva hacnvagrq gb gur ynfg. Gehr, bar cbegenvg znl uvg
the mark much nearer than another, but none can hit it with any very            gur znex zhpu arnere guna nabgure, ohg abar pna uvg vg jvgu nal irel
considerable degree of exactness. So there is no earthly way of finding         pbafvqrenoyr qrterr bs rknpgarff. Fb gurer vf ab rneguyl jnl bs svaqvat
out precisely what the whale really looks like. And the only mode in            bhg cerpvfryl jung gur junyr ernyyl ybbxf yvxr. Naq gur bayl zbqr va
which you can derive even a tolerable idea of his living contour, is            juvpu lbh pna qrevir rira n gbyrenoyr vqrn bs uvf yvivat pbagbhe, vf
by going a whaling yourself; but by so doing, you run no small risk of          ol tbvat n junyvat lbhefrys; ohg ol fb qbvat, lbh eha ab fznyy evfx bs
being eternally stove and sunk by him. Wherefore, it seems to me you had        orvat rgreanyyl fgbir naq fhax ol uvz. Jurersber, vg frrzf gb zr lbh unq
best not be too fastidious in your curiosity touching this Leviathan.           orfg abg or gbb snfgvqvbhf va lbhe phevbfvgl gbhpuvat guvf Yrivnguna.
                                                                                
                                                                                
                                                                                
