On Tower-hill, as you go down to the London docks, you may have seen a          Ba Gbjre-uvyy, nf lbh tb qbja gb gur Ybaqba qbpxf, lbh znl unir frra n
crippled beggar (or KEDGER, as the sailors say) holding a painted board         pevccyrq orttne (be XRQTRE, nf gur fnvybef fnl) ubyqvat n cnvagrq obneq
