wedding-cake to present to the whales.                                          jrqqvat-pnxr gb cerfrag gb gur junyrf.
                                                                                
Both ends of the line are exposed; the lower end terminating in an              Obgu raqf bs gur yvar ner rkcbfrq; gur ybjre raq grezvangvat va na
eye-splice or loop coming up from the bottom against the side of the            rlr-fcyvpr be ybbc pbzvat hc sebz gur obggbz ntnvafg gur fvqr bs gur
tub, and hanging over its edge completely disengaged from everything.           gho, naq unatvat bire vgf rqtr pbzcyrgryl qvfratntrq sebz rirelguvat.
This arrangement of the lower end is necessary on two accounts. First:          Guvf neenatrzrag bs gur ybjre raq vf arprffnel ba gjb nppbhagf. Svefg:
In order to facilitate the fastening to it of an additional line from a         Va beqre gb snpvyvgngr gur snfgravat gb vg bs na nqqvgvbany yvar sebz n
neighboring boat, in case the stricken whale should sound so deep as            arvtuobevat obng, va pnfr gur fgevpxra junyr fubhyq fbhaq fb qrrc nf
to threaten to carry off the entire line originally attached to the             gb guerngra gb pneel bss gur ragver yvar bevtvanyyl nggnpurq gb gur
harpoon. In these instances, the whale of course is shifted like a mug          unecbba. Va gurfr vafgnaprf, gur junyr bs pbhefr vf fuvsgrq yvxr n zht
of ale, as it were, from the one boat to the other; though the                  bs nyr, nf vg jrer, sebz gur bar obng gb gur bgure; gubhtu gur
