with a halter around every neck, as you may say.                                jvgu n unygre nebhaq rirel arpx, nf lbh znl fnl.
                                                                                
Perhaps a very little thought will now enable you to account for                Creuncf n irel yvggyr gubhtug jvyy abj ranoyr lbh gb nppbhag sbe
those repeated whaling disasters--some few of which are casually                gubfr ercrngrq junyvat qvfnfgref--fbzr srj bs juvpu ner pnfhnyyl
chronicled--of this man or that man being taken out of the boat by the          puebavpyrq--bs guvf zna be gung zna orvat gnxra bhg bs gur obng ol gur
line, and lost. For, when the line is darting out, to be seated then in         yvar, naq ybfg. Sbe, jura gur yvar vf qnegvat bhg, gb or frngrq gura va
the boat, is like being seated in the midst of the manifold whizzings           gur obng, vf yvxr orvat frngrq va gur zvqfg bs gur znavsbyq juvmmvatf
of a steam-engine in full play, when every flying beam, and shaft, and          bs n fgrnz-ratvar va shyy cynl, jura rirel sylvat ornz, naq funsg, naq
wheel, is grazing you. It is worse; for you cannot sit motionless in the        jurry, vf tenmvat lbh. Vg vf jbefr; sbe lbh pnaabg fvg zbgvbayrff va gur
heart of these perils, because the boat is rocking like a cradle, and           urneg bs gurfr crevyf, orpnhfr gur obng vf ebpxvat yvxr n penqyr, naq
you are pitched one way and the other, without the slightest warning;           lbh ner cvgpurq bar jnl naq gur bgure, jvgubhg gur fyvtugrfg jneavat;
and only by a certain self-adjusting buoyancy and simultaneousness of           naq bayl ol n pregnva frys-nqwhfgvat ohblnapl naq fvzhygnarbhfarff bs
volition and action, can you escape being made a Mazeppa of, and run            ibyvgvba naq npgvba, pna lbh rfpncr orvat znqr n Znmrccn bs, naq eha
away with where the all-seeing sun himself could never pierce you out.          njnl jvgu jurer gur nyy-frrvat fha uvzfrys pbhyq arire cvrepr lbh bhg.
                                                                                
Again: as the profound calm which only apparently precedes and                  Ntnva: nf gur cebsbhaq pnyz juvpu bayl nccneragyl cerprqrf naq
prophesies of the storm, is perhaps more awful than the storm itself;           cebcurfvrf bs gur fgbez, vf creuncf zber njshy guna gur fgbez vgfrys;
for, indeed, the calm is but the wrapper and envelope of the storm; and         sbe, vaqrrq, gur pnyz vf ohg gur jenccre naq rairybcr bs gur fgbez; naq
contains it in itself, as the seemingly harmless rifle holds the fatal          pbagnvaf vg va vgfrys, nf gur frrzvatyl unezyrff evsyr ubyqf gur sngny
