of fact these are no arguments against such a presumption; because you          bs snpg gurfr ner ab nethzragf ntnvafg fhpu n cerfhzcgvba; orpnhfr lbh
cannot raise any other dense enveloping layer from the whale's body but         pnaabg envfr nal bgure qrafr rairybcvat ynlre sebz gur junyr'f obql ohg
that same blubber; and the outermost enveloping layer of any animal, if         gung fnzr oyhoore; naq gur bhgrezbfg rairybcvat ynlre bs nal navzny, vs
reasonably dense, what can that be but the skin? True, from the unmarred        ernfbanoyl qrafr, jung pna gung or ohg gur fxva? Gehr, sebz gur hazneerq
dead body of the whale, you may scrape off with your hand an infinitely         qrnq obql bs gur junyr, lbh znl fpencr bss jvgu lbhe unaq na vasvavgryl
