CHAPTER 74. The Sperm Whale's Head--Contrasted View.                            PUNCGRE 74. Gur Fcrez Junyr'f Urnq--Pbagenfgrq Ivrj.
                                                                                
                                                                                
Here, now, are two great whales, laying their heads together; let us            Urer, abj, ner gjb terng junyrf, ynlvat gurve urnqf gbtrgure; yrg hf
join them, and lay together our own.                                            wbva gurz, naq ynl gbtrgure bhe bja.
                                                                                
Of the grand order of folio leviathans, the Sperm Whale and the Right           Bs gur tenaq beqre bs sbyvb yrivngunaf, gur Fcrez Junyr naq gur Evtug
Whale are by far the most noteworthy. They are the only whales regularly        Junyr ner ol sne gur zbfg abgrjbegul. Gurl ner gur bayl junyrf erthyneyl
hunted by man. To the Nantucketer, they present the two extremes of all         uhagrq ol zna. Gb gur Anaghpxrgre, gurl cerfrag gur gjb rkgerzrf bs nyy
the known varieties of the whale. As the external difference between            gur xabja inevrgvrf bs gur junyr. Nf gur rkgreany qvssrerapr orgjrra
them is mainly observable in their heads; and as a head of each is this         gurz vf znvayl bofreinoyr va gurve urnqf; naq nf n urnq bs rnpu vf guvf
moment hanging from the Pequod's side; and as we may freely go from one         zbzrag unatvat sebz gur Crdhbq'f fvqr; naq nf jr znl serryl tb sebz bar
to the other, by merely stepping across the deck:--where, I should like         gb gur bgure, ol zreryl fgrccvat npebff gur qrpx:--jurer, V fubhyq yvxr
to know, will you obtain a better chance to study practical cetology            gb xabj, jvyy lbh bognva n orggre punapr gb fghql cenpgvpny prgbybtl
