wall of a thick tendinous substance.                                            jnyy bs n guvpx graqvabhf fhofgnapr.
                                                                                
                                                                                
*Quoin is not a Euclidean term. It belongs to the pure nautical                 *Dhbva vf abg n Rhpyvqrna grez. Vg orybatf gb gur cher anhgvpny
mathematics. I know not that it has been defined before. A quoin is a           zngurzngvpf. V xabj abg gung vg unf orra qrsvarq orsber. N dhbva vf n
solid which differs from a wedge in having its sharp end formed by the          fbyvq juvpu qvssref sebz n jrqtr va univat vgf funec raq sbezrq ol gur
