to be rehearsed from the Shaster, which gives us the dread Vishnoo, one         gb or erurnefrq sebz gur Funfgre, juvpu tvirf hf gur qernq Ivfuabb, bar
of the three persons in the godhead of the Hindoos; gives us this divine        bs gur guerr crefbaf va gur tbqurnq bs gur Uvaqbbf; tvirf hf guvf qvivar
Vishnoo himself for our Lord;--Vishnoo, who, by the first of his ten            Ivfuabb uvzfrys sbe bhe Ybeq;--Ivfuabb, jub, ol gur svefg bs uvf gra
earthly incarnations, has for ever set apart and sanctified the whale.          rneguyl vapneangvbaf, unf sbe rire frg ncneg naq fnapgvsvrq gur junyr.
When Brahma, or the God of Gods, saith the Shaster, resolved to recreate        Jura Oenuzn, be gur Tbq bs Tbqf, fnvgu gur Funfgre, erfbyirq gb erperngr
the world after one of its periodical dissolutions, he gave birth to            gur jbeyq nsgre bar bs vgf crevbqvpny qvffbyhgvbaf, ur tnir ovegu gb
Vishnoo, to preside over the work; but the Vedas, or mystical books,            Ivfuabb, gb cerfvqr bire gur jbex; ohg gur Irqnf, be zlfgvpny obbxf,
whose perusal would seem to have been indispensable to Vishnoo before           jubfr crehfny jbhyq frrz gb unir orra vaqvfcrafnoyr gb Ivfuabb orsber
beginning the creation, and which therefore must have contained                 ortvaavat gur perngvba, naq juvpu gurersber zhfg unir pbagnvarq
something in the shape of practical hints to young architects, these            fbzrguvat va gur funcr bs cenpgvpny uvagf gb lbhat nepuvgrpgf, gurfr
