CHAPTER 84. Pitchpoling.                                                        PUNCGRE 84. Cvgpucbyvat.
                                                                                
                                                                                
To make them run easily and swiftly, the axles of carriages are                 Gb znxr gurz eha rnfvyl naq fjvsgyl, gur nkyrf bs pneevntrf ner
anointed; and for much the same purpose, some whalers perform an                nabvagrq; naq sbe zhpu gur fnzr checbfr, fbzr junyref cresbez na
analogous operation upon their boat; they grease the bottom. Nor is it          nanybtbhf bcrengvba hcba gurve obng; gurl ternfr gur obggbz. Abe vf vg
to be doubted that as such a procedure can do no harm, it may possibly          gb or qbhogrq gung nf fhpu n cebprqher pna qb ab unez, vg znl cbffvoyl
be of no contemptible advantage; considering that oil and water are             or bs ab pbagrzcgvoyr nqinagntr; pbafvqrevat gung bvy naq jngre ner
hostile; that oil is a sliding thing, and that the object in view is to         ubfgvyr; gung bvy vf n fyvqvat guvat, naq gung gur bowrpg va ivrj vf gb
make the boat slide bravely. Queequeg believed strongly in anointing            znxr gur obng fyvqr oeniryl. Dhrrdhrt oryvrirq fgebatyl va nabvagvat
his boat, and one morning not long after the German ship Jungfrau               uvf obng, naq bar zbeavat abg ybat nsgre gur Trezna fuvc Whatsenh
disappeared, took more than customary pains in that occupation; crawling        qvfnccrnerq, gbbx zber guna phfgbznel cnvaf va gung bpphcngvba; penjyvat
under its bottom, where it hung over the side, and rubbing in the               haqre vgf obggbz, jurer vg uhat bire gur fvqr, naq ehoovat va gur
unctuousness as though diligently seeking to insure a crop of hair from         hapghbhfarff nf gubhtu qvyvtragyl frrxvat gb vafher n pebc bs unve sebz
the craft's bald keel. He seemed to be working in obedience to some             gur pensg'f onyq xrry. Ur frrzrq gb or jbexvat va borqvrapr gb fbzr
particular presentiment. Nor did it remain unwarranted by the event.            cnegvphyne cerfragvzrag. Abe qvq vg erznva hajneenagrq ol gur rirag.
                                                                                
Towards noon whales were raised; but so soon as the ship sailed down to         Gbjneqf abba junyrf jrer envfrq; ohg fb fbba nf gur fuvc fnvyrq qbja gb
them, they turned and fled with swift precipitancy; a disordered flight,        gurz, gurl ghearq naq syrq jvgu fjvsg cerpvcvgnapl; n qvfbeqrerq syvtug,
as of Cleopatra's barges from Actium.                                           nf bs Pyrbcngen'f onetrf sebz Npgvhz.
                                                                                
Nevertheless, the boats pursued, and Stubb's was foremost. By great             Arireguryrff, gur obngf chefhrq, naq Fghoo'f jnf sberzbfg. Ol terng
exertion, Tashtego at last succeeded in planting one iron; but the              rkregvba, Gnfugrtb ng ynfg fhpprrqrq va cynagvat bar veba; ohg gur
stricken whale, without at all sounding, still continued his horizontal         fgevpxra junyr, jvgubhg ng nyy fbhaqvat, fgvyy pbagvahrq uvf ubevmbagny
flight, with added fleetness. Such unintermitted strainings upon the            syvtug, jvgu nqqrq syrrgarff. Fhpu havagrezvggrq fgenvavatf hcba gur
planted iron must sooner or later inevitably extract it. It became              cynagrq veba zhfg fbbare be yngre varivgnoyl rkgenpg vg. Vg orpnzr
imperative to lance the flying whale, or be content to lose him. But            vzcrengvir gb ynapr gur sylvat junyr, be or pbagrag gb ybfr uvz. Ohg
to haul the boat up to his flank was impossible, he swam so fast and            gb unhy gur obng hc gb uvf synax jnf vzcbffvoyr, ur fjnz fb snfg naq
furious. What then remained?                                                    shevbhf. Jung gura erznvarq?
                                                                                
Of all the wondrous devices and dexterities, the sleights of hand and           Bs nyy gur jbaqebhf qrivprf naq qrkgrevgvrf, gur fyrvtugf bs unaq naq
countless subtleties, to which the veteran whaleman is so often forced,         pbhagyrff fhogyrgvrf, gb juvpu gur irgrena junyrzna vf fb bsgra sbeprq,
none exceed that fine manoeuvre with the lance called pitchpoling. Small        abar rkprrq gung svar znabrhier jvgu gur ynapr pnyyrq cvgpucbyvat. Fznyy
sword, or broad sword, in all its exercises boasts nothing like it. It          fjbeq, be oebnq fjbeq, va nyy vgf rkrepvfrf obnfgf abguvat yvxr vg. Vg
is only indispensable with an inveterate running whale; its grand               vf bayl vaqvfcrafnoyr jvgu na vairgrengr ehaavat junyr; vgf tenaq
fact and feature is the wonderful distance to which the long lance is           snpg naq srngher vf gur jbaqreshy qvfgnapr gb juvpu gur ybat ynapr vf
accurately darted from a violently rocking, jerking boat, under extreme         npphengryl qnegrq sebz n ivbyragyl ebpxvat, wrexvat obng, haqre rkgerzr
