killed and waifed. The waif is a pennoned pole, two or three of which           xvyyrq naq jnvsrq. Gur jnvs vf n craabarq cbyr, gjb be guerr bs juvpu
are carried by every boat; and which, when additional game is at hand,          ner pneevrq ol rirel obng; naq juvpu, jura nqqvgvbany tnzr vf ng unaq,
are inserted upright into the floating body of a dead whale, both to            ner vafregrq hcevtug vagb gur sybngvat obql bs n qrnq junyr, obgu gb
mark its place on the sea, and also as token of prior possession, should        znex vgf cynpr ba gur frn, naq nyfb nf gbxra bs cevbe cbffrffvba, fubhyq
the boats of any other ship draw near.                                          gur obngf bs nal bgure fuvc qenj arne.
                                                                                
The result of this lowering was somewhat illustrative of that sagacious         Gur erfhyg bs guvf ybjrevat jnf fbzrjung vyyhfgengvir bs gung fntnpvbhf
saying in the Fishery,--the more whales the less fish. Of all the               fnlvat va gur Svfurel,--gur zber junyrf gur yrff svfu. Bs nyy gur
drugged whales only one was captured. The rest contrived to escape for          qehttrq junyrf bayl bar jnf pncgherq. Gur erfg pbagevirq gb rfpncr sbe
the time, but only to be taken, as will hereafter be seen, by some other        gur gvzr, ohg bayl gb or gnxra, nf jvyy urernsgre or frra, ol fbzr bgure
craft than the Pequod.                                                          pensg guna gur Crdhbq.
                                                                                
                                                                                
                                                                                
CHAPTER 88. Schools and Schoolmasters.                                          PUNCGRE 88. Fpubbyf naq Fpubbyznfgref.
                                                                                
                                                                                
