CHAPTER 89. Fast-Fish and Loose-Fish.                                           PUNCGRE 89. Snfg-Svfu naq Ybbfr-Svfu.
                                                                                
                                                                                
The allusion to the waif and waif-poles in the last chapter but one,            Gur nyyhfvba gb gur jnvs naq jnvs-cbyrf va gur ynfg puncgre ohg bar,
necessitates some account of the laws and regulations of the whale              arprffvgngrf fbzr nppbhag bs gur ynjf naq erthyngvbaf bs gur junyr
fishery, of which the waif may be deemed the grand symbol and badge.            svfurel, bs juvpu gur jnvs znl or qrrzrq gur tenaq flzoby naq onqtr.
                                                                                
It frequently happens that when several ships are cruising in company,          Vg serdhragyl unccraf gung jura frireny fuvcf ner pehvfvat va pbzcnal,
a whale may be struck by one vessel, then escape, and be finally killed         n junyr znl or fgehpx ol bar irffry, gura rfpncr, naq or svanyyl xvyyrq
and captured by another vessel; and herein are indirectly comprised             naq pncgherq ol nabgure irffry; naq urerva ner vaqverpgyl pbzcevfrq
many minor contingencies, all partaking of this one grand feature. For          znal zvabe pbagvatrapvrf, nyy cnegnxvat bs guvf bar tenaq srngher. Sbe
example,--after a weary and perilous chase and capture of a whale,              rknzcyr,--nsgre n jrnel naq crevybhf punfr naq pncgher bs n junyr,
the body may get loose from the ship by reason of a violent storm; and          gur obql znl trg ybbfr sebz gur fuvc ol ernfba bs n ivbyrag fgbez; naq
drifting far away to leeward, be retaken by a second whaler, who, in a          qevsgvat sne njnl gb yrrjneq, or ergnxra ol n frpbaq junyre, jub, va n
calm, snugly tows it alongside, without risk of life or line. Thus              pnyz, fahtyl gbjf vg nybatfvqr, jvgubhg evfx bs yvsr be yvar. Guhf
the most vexatious and violent disputes would often arise between               gur zbfg irkngvbhf naq ivbyrag qvfchgrf jbhyq bsgra nevfr orgjrra
the fishermen, were there not some written or unwritten, universal,             gur svfurezra, jrer gurer abg fbzr jevggra be hajevggra, havirefny,
undisputed law applicable to all cases.                                         haqvfchgrq ynj nccyvpnoyr gb nyy pnfrf.
                                                                                
Perhaps the only formal whaling code authorized by legislative                  Creuncf gur bayl sbezny junyvat pbqr nhgubevmrq ol yrtvfyngvir
enactment, was that of Holland. It was decreed by the States-General in         ranpgzrag, jnf gung bs Ubyynaq. Vg jnf qrperrq ol gur Fgngrf-Trareny va
A.D. 1695. But though no other nation has ever had any written whaling          N.Q. 1695. Ohg gubhtu ab bgure angvba unf rire unq nal jevggra junyvat
law, yet the American fishermen have been their own legislators and             ynj, lrg gur Nzrevpna svfurezra unir orra gurve bja yrtvfyngbef naq
lawyers in this matter. They have provided a system which for terse             ynjlref va guvf znggre. Gurl unir cebivqrq n flfgrz juvpu sbe grefr
comprehensiveness surpasses Justinian's Pandects and the By-laws of             pbzcerurafvirarff fhecnffrf Whfgvavna'f Cnaqrpgf naq gur Ol-ynjf bs
the Chinese Society for the Suppression of Meddling with other People's         gur Puvarfr Fbpvrgl sbe gur Fhccerffvba bs Zrqqyvat jvgu bgure Crbcyr'f
Business. Yes; these laws might be engraven on a Queen Anne's farthing,         Ohfvarff. Lrf; gurfr ynjf zvtug or ratenira ba n Dhrra Naar'f sneguvat,
or the barb of a harpoon, and worn round the neck, so small are they.           be gur oneo bs n unecbba, naq jbea ebhaq gur arpx, fb fznyy ner gurl.
                                                                                
I. A Fast-Fish belongs to the party fast to it.                                 V. N Snfg-Svfu orybatf gb gur cnegl snfg gb vg.
                                                                                
II. A Loose-Fish is fair game for anybody who can soonest catch it.             VV. N Ybbfr-Svfu vf snve tnzr sbe nalobql jub pna fbbarfg pngpu vg.
                                                                                
But what plays the mischief with this masterly code is the admirable            Ohg jung cynlf gur zvfpuvrs jvgu guvf znfgreyl pbqr vf gur nqzvenoyr
brevity of it, which necessitates a vast volume of commentaries to              oerivgl bs vg, juvpu arprffvgngrf n infg ibyhzr bs pbzzragnevrf gb
expound it.                                                                     rkcbhaq vg.
                                                                                
First: What is a Fast-Fish? Alive or dead a fish is technically fast,           Svefg: Jung vf n Snfg-Svfu? Nyvir be qrnq n svfu vf grpuavpnyyl snfg,
when it is connected with an occupied ship or boat, by any medium at all        jura vg vf pbaarpgrq jvgu na bpphcvrq fuvc be obng, ol nal zrqvhz ng nyy
controllable by the occupant or occupants,--a mast, an oar, a nine-inch         pbagebyynoyr ol gur bpphcnag be bpphcnagf,--n znfg, na bne, n avar-vapu
cable, a telegraph wire, or a strand of cobweb, it is all the same.             pnoyr, n gryrtencu jver, be n fgenaq bs pbojro, vg vf nyy gur fnzr.
Likewise a fish is technically fast when it bears a waif, or any other          Yvxrjvfr n svfu vf grpuavpnyyl snfg jura vg ornef n jnvs, be nal bgure
recognised symbol of possession; so long as the party waifing it plainly        erpbtavfrq flzoby bs cbffrffvba; fb ybat nf gur cnegl jnvsvat vg cynvayl
evince their ability at any time to take it alongside, as well as their         rivapr gurve novyvgl ng nal gvzr gb gnxr vg nybatfvqr, nf jryy nf gurve
intention so to do.                                                             vagragvba fb gb qb.
                                                                                
These are scientific commentaries; but the commentaries of the whalemen         Gurfr ner fpvragvsvp pbzzragnevrf; ohg gur pbzzragnevrf bs gur junyrzra
themselves sometimes consist in hard words and harder knocks--the               gurzfryirf fbzrgvzrf pbafvfg va uneq jbeqf naq uneqre xabpxf--gur
