CHAPTER 101. The Decanter.                                                      PUNCGRE 101. Gur Qrpnagre.
                                                                                
                                                                                
Ere the English ship fades from sight, be it set down here, that                Rer gur Ratyvfu fuvc snqrf sebz fvtug, or vg frg qbja urer, gung
she hailed from London, and was named after the late Samuel Enderby,            fur unvyrq sebz Ybaqba, naq jnf anzrq nsgre gur yngr Fnzhry Raqreol,
merchant of that city, the original of the famous whaling house of              zrepunag bs gung pvgl, gur bevtvany bs gur snzbhf junyvat ubhfr bs
Enderby & Sons; a house which in my poor whaleman's opinion, comes not          Raqreol & Fbaf; n ubhfr juvpu va zl cbbe junyrzna'f bcvavba, pbzrf abg
far behind the united royal houses of the Tudors and Bourbons, in point         sne oruvaq gur havgrq eblny ubhfrf bs gur Ghqbef naq Obheobaf, va cbvag
of real historical interest. How long, prior to the year of our                 bs erny uvfgbevpny vagrerfg. Ubj ybat, cevbe gb gur lrne bs bhe
Lord 1775, this great whaling house was in existence, my numerous               Ybeq 1775, guvf terng junyvat ubhfr jnf va rkvfgrapr, zl ahzrebhf
fish-documents do not make plain; but in that year (1775) it fitted             svfu-qbphzragf qb abg znxr cynva; ohg va gung lrne (1775) vg svggrq
out the first English ships that ever regularly hunted the Sperm Whale;         bhg gur svefg Ratyvfu fuvcf gung rire erthyneyl uhagrq gur Fcrez Junyr;
though for some score of years previous (ever since 1726) our valiant           gubhtu sbe fbzr fpber bs lrnef cerivbhf (rire fvapr 1726) bhe inyvnag
Coffins and Maceys of Nantucket and the Vineyard had in large fleets            Pbssvaf naq Znprlf bs Anaghpxrg naq gur Ivarlneq unq va ynetr syrrgf
pursued that Leviathan, but only in the North and South Atlantic: not           chefhrq gung Yrivnguna, ohg bayl va gur Abegu naq Fbhgu Ngynagvp: abg
elsewhere. Be it distinctly recorded here, that the Nantucketers were           ryfrjurer. Or vg qvfgvapgyl erpbeqrq urer, gung gur Anaghpxrgref jrer
the first among mankind to harpoon with civilized steel the great Sperm         gur svefg nzbat znaxvaq gb unecbba jvgu pvivyvmrq fgrry gur terng Fcrez
Whale; and that for half a century they were the only people of the             Junyr; naq gung sbe unys n praghel gurl jrer gur bayl crbcyr bs gur
whole globe who so harpooned him.                                               jubyr tybor jub fb unecbbarq uvz.
                                                                                
In 1778, a fine ship, the Amelia, fitted out for the express purpose,           Va 1778, n svar fuvc, gur Nzryvn, svggrq bhg sbe gur rkcerff checbfr,
and at the sole charge of the vigorous Enderbys, boldly rounded Cape            naq ng gur fbyr punetr bs gur ivtbebhf Raqreolf, obyqyl ebhaqrq Pncr
Horn, and was the first among the nations to lower a whale-boat of any          Ubea, naq jnf gur svefg nzbat gur angvbaf gb ybjre n junyr-obng bs nal
sort in the great South Sea. The voyage was a skilful and lucky one;            fbeg va gur terng Fbhgu Frn. Gur iblntr jnf n fxvyshy naq yhpxl bar;
and returning to her berth with her hold full of the precious sperm, the        naq ergheavat gb ure oregu jvgu ure ubyq shyy bs gur cerpvbhf fcrez, gur
Amelia's example was soon followed by other ships, English and American,        Nzryvn'f rknzcyr jnf fbba sbyybjrq ol bgure fuvcf, Ratyvfu naq Nzrevpna,
and thus the vast Sperm Whale grounds of the Pacific were thrown open.          naq guhf gur infg Fcrez Junyr tebhaqf bs gur Cnpvsvp jrer guebja bcra.
But not content with this good deed, the indefatigable house again              Ohg abg pbagrag jvgu guvf tbbq qrrq, gur vaqrsngvtnoyr ubhfr ntnva
bestirred itself: Samuel and all his Sons--how many, their mother only          orfgveerq vgfrys: Fnzhry naq nyy uvf Fbaf--ubj znal, gurve zbgure bayl
