CHAPTER 106. Ahab's Leg.                                                        PUNCGRE 106. Nuno'f Yrt.
                                                                                
                                                                                
The precipitating manner in which Captain Ahab had quitted the Samuel           Gur cerpvcvgngvat znaare va juvpu Pncgnva Nuno unq dhvggrq gur Fnzhry
Enderby of London, had not been unattended with some small violence to          Raqreol bs Ybaqba, unq abg orra hanggraqrq jvgu fbzr fznyy ivbyrapr gb
his own person. He had lighted with such energy upon a thwart of his            uvf bja crefba. Ur unq yvtugrq jvgu fhpu raretl hcba n gujneg bs uvf
boat that his ivory leg had received a half-splintering shock. And              obng gung uvf vibel yrt unq erprvirq n unys-fcyvagrevat fubpx. Naq
when after gaining his own deck, and his own pivot-hole there, he so            jura nsgre tnvavat uvf bja qrpx, naq uvf bja cvibg-ubyr gurer, ur fb
vehemently wheeled round with an urgent command to the steersman (it            irurzragyl jurryrq ebhaq jvgu na hetrag pbzznaq gb gur fgrrefzna (vg
was, as ever, something about his not steering inflexibly enough); then,        jnf, nf rire, fbzrguvat nobhg uvf abg fgrrevat vasyrkvoyl rabhtu); gura,
the already shaken ivory received such an additional twist and wrench,          gur nyernql funxra vibel erprvirq fhpu na nqqvgvbany gjvfg naq jerapu,
that though it still remained entire, and to all appearances lusty, yet         gung gubhtu vg fgvyy erznvarq ragver, naq gb nyy nccrnenaprf yhfgl, lrg
Ahab did not deem it entirely trustworthy.                                      Nuno qvq abg qrrz vg ragveryl gehfgjbegul.
                                                                                
And, indeed, it seemed small matter for wonder, that for all his                Naq, vaqrrq, vg frrzrq fznyy znggre sbe jbaqre, gung sbe nyy uvf
pervading, mad recklessness, Ahab did at times give careful heed to the         creinqvat, znq erpxyrffarff, Nuno qvq ng gvzrf tvir pnershy urrq gb gur
condition of that dead bone upon which he partly stood. For it had not          pbaqvgvba bs gung qrnq obar hcba juvpu ur cnegyl fgbbq. Sbe vg unq abg
been very long prior to the Pequod's sailing from Nantucket, that he            orra irel ybat cevbe gb gur Crdhbq'f fnvyvat sebz Anaghpxrg, gung ur
had been found one night lying prone upon the ground, and insensible;           unq orra sbhaq bar avtug ylvat cebar hcba gur tebhaq, naq vafrafvoyr;
by some unknown, and seemingly inexplicable, unimaginable casualty, his         ol fbzr haxabja, naq frrzvatyl varkcyvpnoyr, havzntvanoyr pnfhnygl, uvf
ivory limb having been so violently displaced, that it had stake-wise           vibel yvzo univat orra fb ivbyragyl qvfcynprq, gung vg unq fgnxr-jvfr
smitten, and all but pierced his groin; nor was it without extreme              fzvggra, naq nyy ohg cvreprq uvf tebva; abe jnf vg jvgubhg rkgerzr
difficulty that the agonizing wound was entirely cured.                         qvssvphygl gung gur ntbavmvat jbhaq jnf ragveryl pherq.
                                                                                
Nor, at the time, had it failed to enter his monomaniac mind, that all          Abe, ng gur gvzr, unq vg snvyrq gb ragre uvf zbabznavnp zvaq, gung nyy
