CHAPTER 107. The Carpenter.                                                     PUNCGRE 107. Gur Pnecragre.
                                                                                
                                                                                
Seat thyself sultanically among the moons of Saturn, and take high              Frng gulfrys fhygnavpnyyl nzbat gur zbbaf bs Fnghea, naq gnxr uvtu
abstracted man alone; and he seems a wonder, a grandeur, and a woe. But         nofgenpgrq zna nybar; naq ur frrzf n jbaqre, n tenaqrhe, naq n jbr. Ohg
